JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 964
EP  - 974
VL  - 33
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - I discuss the implications of postcolonial studies for examining and expanding the study of international management. First, I outline various debates and approaches within the postcolonial field. Following this, I summarize key theoretical concepts emanating from three seminal postcolonial scholars?Said, Spivak, and Bhabha? whose works have helped define the field. I rely on each of their lenses?Orientalism, gendered postcolonial subject, and hybridity, respectively?to discuss possibilities and new directions for international management research.
AB  - I discuss the implications of postcolonial studies for examining and expanding the study of international management. First, I outline various debates and approaches within the postcolonial field. Following this, I summarize key theoretical concepts emanating from three seminal postcolonial scholars?Said, Spivak, and Bhabha? whose works have helped define the field. I rely on each of their lenses?Orientalism, gendered postcolonial subject, and hybridity, respectively?to discuss possibilities and new directions for international management research.
